The '''Bristol/Bath to South Coast Study''' is a [[transportation study]] initiated by the United Kingdom's [[Government Office for the South West]]<ref name="Wolmar2005">{{cite book|author=Christian Wolmar|title=On the wrong line: how ideology and incompetence wrecked Britain's railways|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dq-3AAAAIAAJ|accessdate=7 June 2013|date=25 September 2005|publisher=Aurum|isbn=978-1-85410-998-9|page=280}}</ref> and [[Bath and North East Somerset Council]] in [[southwest England]].<ref name="gov-news 2004">{{cite news | url=http://www.gov-news.org/gov/uk/news/bristolbath_to_south_coast_study_final_reports/57227.html | title=Bristol/Bath to South Coast Study&nbsp;— final reports published | work=Government News | date=13 February 2004 | accessdate=28 September 2012}}</ref> It was undertaken by [[WSP Group]]<ref name="gov-news 2004" /> as a result of the [[de-trunking]] in 1999 of the A36/A46 trunk road network<ref name="hansard 2004">{{cite web | url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200304/cmhansrd/vo040106/text/40106w02.htm | title=Hansard 6 Jan 2004 : Column 218W | publisher=[[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] | work=[[Hansard]] | date=6 Jan 2004 | accessdate=28 September 2012}}</ref> from [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]] to [[Southampton]]. The final study reports were published in 2004.<ref name="gov-news 2004" />

== Findings ==
The study showed that an A36-A46 link road (to the east of Bath) would significantly reduce [[HGV traffic]] in Bath. It was also shown to reduce traffic volumes in [[Trowbridge]] and [[Bradford on Avon]].<ref name="thisisbath 20120621">{{cite news | url=http://www.thisisbath.co.uk/Councils-work-HGV-problem/story-16428220-detail/story.html#axzz2Tufldk5S | title=Councils must work together on HGV problem | work=[[Bath Chronicle]] | date=21 June 2012 | accessdate=2013-06-07 | author=Federation of Bath Residents' Associations}}</ref> The proposed link road was costed at £40M.<ref name="highbeam 20040422">{{cite news | url=http://business.highbeam.com/435120/article-1G1-115824013/cost-cutting-claims-hit-bath-linkroad | title=Cost cutting claims hit Bath link-road | work=[[Commercial Motor]]| date=22 April 2004 | accessdate=2013-06-07}}{{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}}</ref><ref name="ebscohost 20040422">{{cite news | url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/articles/13117802/cost-cutting-claims-hit-bath-link-road | title=Cost cutting claims hit Bath link-road | last = Nash | first=Sally | work=[[Commercial Motor]]| volume=199 | issue = 5076 | page = 14 | date=22 April 2004 | accessdate=2013-06-07}}{{Subscription required|via=[[EBSCOhost]]}}</ref>

