{{Anthropology of kinship |concepts}}

'''Cognatic kinship''' is a mode of [[Descent (kinship)|descent]] calculated from an [[ancestor]] or ancestress counted through any combination of male and female links, or a system of [[bilateral kinship]] where relations are traced through both a father and mother.<ref>{{cite book |last=Wolters |first=O. W. |year=1999 |title=History, Culture, and Region in Southeast Asian Perspectives |publisher=SEAP Publications |isbn=0-87727-725-7 |page=17}}</ref> Such relatives may be known as '''cognates'''.

