'''IC 1838''' (also known as MCG+03-08-002 or LEDA 10389) is a [[spiral galaxy]] of type '''Sc'''. It lies in the [[Taurus constellation]], 52.42 million [[light years]] away from Earth. It has a diameter of 13,046.5 light years and a thickness of 1,304.7 light years.

