'''Moti Lal Dhar''' ( 22 October 1914 &ndash; 20 January 2002)<ref>http://www.kecss.org/prominent+kashmiris+people+clbhat.html</ref> was an eminent [[medication|drug]] [[chemist]], and [[science]] [[Administration (business)|administrator]] in [[India]]. He remained Director [[Central Drug Research Institute]], [[Lucknow]] from 1960 until his retirement in 1972 and he has been the only [[Kashmiri Pandit]] to serve as Vice- Chancellor, of [[Banaras Hindu University]], B.H.U.<ref>[http://ikashmir.net/gkgurtu/bhu.html Moti Lal Dhar]</ref><ref>[http://www.kecss.org/prominent+kashmiris+people+clbhat.html Prominent Kashmiri people]
</ref>

