{{Infobox scientist | honorific_prefix = | name = Richard J. O'Connell | honorific_suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = |birth_name = Richard John O'Connell | birth_date = {{birth date |1941|08|27}} | birth_place = [[Helena, Montana]] | death_date = {{death date and age |2015|4|2|1941|08|27}} | death_place = [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]] | death_cause = | other_names = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = | institutions = [[Harvard University]] | patrons = | education = | alma_mater = [[California Institute of Technology]] | thesis_title = <!--(or | thesis1_title = and | thesis2_title = )--> | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = <!--(or | thesis1_year = and | thesis2_year = )--> | doctoral_advisor = <!--(or | doctoral_advisors = )--> | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = Geophysics | influences = | influenced = | awards = | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = }} '''Richard John O'Connell''' (August 27, 1941<ref name="cv">{{cite web|title=Curriculum Vitae - Richard J. O'Connell|url=http://projects.iq.harvard.edu/richard-oconnell/biocv/cv|accessdate=22 July 2016}}</ref> – April 2, 2015<ref name="obit">{{cite web|title=Richard John O’Connell dies|url=http://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2015/04/richard-john-oconnell-dies/|publisher=[[Harvard Gazette]]|accessdate=22 July 2016|date=6 April 2015}}</ref>) was an American [[geophysicist]] working on the internal dynamics of the Earth and how they evolved over time and are observed at the surface. He received his B.S., M.S., and Ph.D. degrees from [[California Institute of Technology]],<ref name="cv"/> and spent most of his further academic career at [[Harvard University]].
O'Connell received the [[Inge Lehmann Medal]] from [[American Geophysical Union]] in 2000,<ref>{{cite web|title=Richard J. O'Connell - Honors Program|url=https://honors.agu.org/winners/richard-j-oconnell/|website=AGU Honors Program|publisher=American Geophysical Union|accessdate=22 July 2016}}</ref> the [[Arthur L. Day Medal]] from [[Geological Society of America]] in 2001,<ref name=obit/> and the Augustus Love Medal from the [[European Geosciences Union]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=EGU - Awards & Medals - Augustus Love Medal - Richard J. O'Connell|url=http://www.egu.eu/awards-medals/augustus-love/2008/richard-j-oconnell/|website=EGU|publisher=[[European Geosciences Union]]|accessdate=22 July 2016}}</ref> He was a fellow of the [[American Geophysical Union]],<ref name="cobit">{{cite web|author1=Jessica Kim|author2=Steven Tenzer|title=Long-Time EPS Professor Richard O’Connell Dies at 73|url=http://www.thecrimson.com/article/2015/4/8/eps-professor-oconnell-passes/|website=thecrimson.com|publisher=[[Harvard Crimson]]|accessdate=22 July 2016|date=8 April 2015}}</ref> the [[American Association for the Advancement of Science]],<ref name="cobit"/> and [[American Academy of Arts and Sciences]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kelley|first1=Kara|title=Twelve Professors Join Select Academy|url=http://www.thecrimson.com/article/2007/5/2/twelve-professors-join-select-academy-twelve/|website=thecrimson.com|publisher=[[Harvard Crimson]]|accessdate=22 July 2016|date=2 May 2007}}</ref>
